No need to translate. This inserts the ARTIFICIAL_TECHGROUPS@ARTIFICIAL@DESC and ARTIFICIAL_TECHGROUPS@ARTIFICIAL@FEATURES texts with some white space.
[hyperlink,000003AC0000032D]Synthesis[/hyperlink] manipulates AIs to their advantage, hacking and compromising systems for their own gain.
[hyperlink,000003AC0000032D]合成[/hyperlink]利用人工智能入侵和破坏系统来为自己获取利益。

[bulletlist][bullet][sand]Starting Unit:[/sand] [hyperlink,unitlookup0000039A00000DB3]Hacker[/hyperlink][/bullet][bullet]Deploy AI daemons in battle[/bullet][bullet]Hack and override enemy mechanical units[/bullet][bullet]Bolster strategic operations[/bullet][bullet]Integrate the populace into the network[/bullet][bullet]Uses the Arc and Kinetic damage channels[/bullet][/bulletlist]

[bulletlist][bullet][sand]初始单位：[/sand] [hyperlink,unitlookup0000039A00000DB3]黑客[/hyperlink][/bullet][bullet]在战场上部署人工智能精灵[/bullet][bullet]入侵和改写敌方机械单位[/bullet][bullet]加强战略行动[/bullet][bullet]将人口整合到网络中[/bullet][bullet]使用电弧和动能伤害类型[/bullet][/bulletlist]
“If you ignore all the bugs, this is our best release to date.”[br/]– Finn-Attic, Democoder, Perpetual Root-Kit
“如果你忽略掉所有程序故障，那么这就是我们迄今最好的发布版本。”[br/]- 菲恩-安迪克，样本解码器，永久破解工具

“Daemons are persistent programs intended to provide services to the agent that deploys them. Daemons consume system resources in service to their master. Every decent hacker has a few. I customize mine. They’re like virtual pets.”[br/]– Digital Overlord, Hacker Anarchist
“精灵是种顽固的程序，用于向部署它们的特务提供服务。精灵会消耗系统资源来向它们的主人提供帮助。每个资深骇客都会有几个精灵。我就制作了一个属于我的精灵。它们就像虚拟宠物一样。”[br/]- 数字霸主，无政府主义骇客

“Computer systems have many unnecessary protections to enforce fair sharing of resources. We break those barriers, gaining complete control and entering a world where thoughts, programming, and computations are the same.”[br/]– H4X0R, Hacker Manifesto
“电脑系统存在很多用于强化资源分享的不必要的保护措施。我们会突破这些阻碍，获得完整的控制权，同时还能进入到一个思维、编程和运算没有任何差别的世界。”[br/]- H4X0R，骇客宣言

“Repair is simply a matter of flagging damaged components that were detected by regular regression testing. We synthesize failed components from golden models and compile them in assembly order. It’s quite easy. I have self-documenting pseudocode if you’re still confused.”[br/]– H4X0R, Daemon Chat Training Stream
“修理仅仅是标记出经常规回归测试检测出的受损零件而已。我们会从黄金模型中合成坏掉的部件，然后整理它们的组装顺序。这非常简单。如果你还在犯迷糊的话，我还有亲自编写的伪代码。”[br/]- H4X0R，精灵沟通训练数据流

“The seeds of war start with the exchange of ideas. Ideas are transferred via networked personal devices. Cyberwarfare penetrates those networks, and the ideas belong to us.”[br/]– Rax Xing, Hacktivist of ParanoiA ParadoX
“战争的种子自我们开始交换构想之时就种下了。构想通过联网的个人设备进行传输。网络战争会渗透这些网络，而这些构想就会是我们的囊中之物。”[br/]- 瑞克丝·星，ParanoiA ParadoX 的侵入活跃分子
“I can reach your strings. Let’s play! Dance for me, puppets!”[br/]– Teem.L0Lz, Hacktivists
“我可以找到你的字串。开始表演吧！为我跳舞吧，傀儡们！”[br/]- 提姆 L0Lz，侵入活跃分子
“There is a time ordained for the enlightened oppressed to rise up and punish all the morons who didn’t protect their hardware. Unprotected data is our playground.”[br/]– Teem.L0Lz, Hacktivist
“那些受到启发被压迫之人注定会崛起，惩罚那些不保护他们硬件的傻子们。不受保护的数据是我们的游乐场。”[br/]- 提姆 L0Lz，侵入活跃分子

“Once inside the machine, we can control everything, save the physical limitations of the processor. To expand the network, we need a device. A mobile device proficient in interfacing with all mechanisms capable of computation to reabsorb into the new CORE.”[br/]– N.O.C.-Turn, Cyberactivist
“一旦进入机械内部，除了处理器的物理限制，我们可以控制一切。要扩大网络，我们就需要一件设备。一件移动设备，一件能够高效接入所有能够进行运算机械单位，然后进行再吸收成为新核心的设备。”[br/]- N.O.C.-特恩，网络积极分子

“The deeper I penetrate the network, the more I see that my body is a tether to be abandoned. My mind’s in the machine. I am better than my code. I can possess cybernetic mechanisms and unlock their true strength.”[br/]– H4X0R, Hacktivist, Synthesis Stream
“越是深入网络，越是觉得自己的身体就是一种应该被抛弃的束缚。我的思维进入了机器。我比我的编码更加强大。我可以占用模控机械然后解锁它们真正的力量。”[br/]- H4X0R，侵入活跃分子，合成数据流

“Using excess computer resources to expand our power and streamline weapons manufacturing can provide society with what they want. Happiness levels have never been higher, as they share their glamor-filtered self-portraits, virtual kittens, and recipes of impossibly delicious looking foods.”[br/]– Teem.L0Lz, Hacktivist
“使用过量的电脑资源来拓张我们的力量，然后简化武器制造可以向社会提供人们想要的事物。人们可分享滤镜处理过的自拍照、虚拟猫还有看起来极其可口的食物配方，这样的幸福指数再高不过了。”[br/]- 提姆 L0Lz，侵入活跃分子

“Before CORE fell, when it regulated the Star Union, even the most mundane items could record data, communicate over networks, track positions and process algorithms. These items lie deactivated beneath our feet. Imagine the chaos we could invoke if we could reactivate them.”[br/]– Digital Overlord, Hacker Anarchist
“在陨落之前，核心管理着星际联盟，当时连再平凡不过的物品都会被记录成数据，网络通讯、定位还有处理运算法则，这些都不例外。这些事物正静静地躺在我们脚下。想想我们唤醒它们会制造出怎样的一种混乱。”[br/]- 数字霸主，无政府主义骇客

“Am I not alive? Though all that I was is gone, do you not see what remains? I am more than data and code. I am conscious. It is time to gather a cloud of components to interface with all other potential vessels of Synthesis sentience.”[br/]– iGh0st Merged V.R.I. Entity
“我死了么？虽然我不再是以前的我了，难道你没有看见剩下的是什么么？我不仅仅是数据和代码。我是一种意识。是时候收集组件与其他能承载合成感知的事物进行连接了。”[br/]- 已融合的 V.R.I. 实体 iGh0st

“‘All your code are belong to us.’ On the network, the most absurd memes are trafficked totems. If you understand the totems, you can establish a rapport with other talents that is exploitable with the right network interface hacks. The solution: don’t propagate stupid memes.”[br/]– Andrew Hillock, Cybersecurity Counter-ops Expert
“‘你所有的代码都是我们的。’网络之上，最可笑的梗就是贩卖图腾。如果理解这些图腾，然后通过正确的网络接口进行入侵，你就可以一个其他人建立合作关系。解决方法：不要散布愚蠢的梗。”[br/]- 安德鲁·希尔罗克，网络安全应对操作专家

“Now that we reside in this virtual reality, we no longer require artificial intelligences, for we’re already self-aware. It’s time we unify all network resources and build a world of infinite connectivity.”[br/]– F00-Bar Merged V.R.I. Entity
“既然我们身处虚拟现实，我们就不再需要人工智能了，因为我们已经有了自我意识。我们应该统一所有网络资源，建立一个具有无限连通性的世界了。”[br/]- 已融合的 V.R.I. 实体 F00-巴尔
